[[File:Ashgabat-Flagpole-2015.JPG|thumb|right|300px|The Ashgabat Flagpole, one of the tallest on Earth]]
The '''Ashgabat Flagpole''' is the 5th tallest free-standing [[flagpole]] in the world, at {{Convert|133|m|ft|0|abbr=off}} tall. It is located in [[Ashgabat]], [[Turkmenistan]], and was erected on 26 June 2008. It has since been surpassed in height by the {{Convert|160|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} [[Panmunjeom flagpole]] ([[North Korea]]), the {{Convert|162|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} [[National Flag Square|National Flagpole]] ([[Azerbaijan]]), the {{Convert|165|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} [[Dushanbe Flagpole]] ([[Tajikistan]]), and since October 2014 the {{Convert|170|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} [[Jeddah Flagpole]].

