{{about|a Belgian skyscraper |the Astrotower, an American amusement ride in Coney Island|Astroland}} {{Infobox building | name = Astro Tower | image = Astrotoren.jpg | image_size = 250px | caption = The Astro Tower, with [[Madou Plaza]] in the background | location = [[Brussels]], [[Belgium]] | coordinates = {{coord|50|51|4|N|4|22|11|E|region:BE|display=inline,title}} | start_date = 1972 | completion_date = 1976<ref name=emporis/> | building_type = Office | roof = {{convert|107|m}}<ref name=emporis/> | floor_count = 31<ref name=emporis>{{cite web|url=http://www.emporis.com/application/?nav=building&lng=3&id=astrotower-brussels-belgium |title=Astro Tower, Brussels at Emporis |location=Brussels |publisher=Emporis.com |date= |accessdate=2013-04-12}}</ref> | floor_area = {{convert|36800|m2}}<ref name = lesoir/> | architect = }}
The '''Astro Tower''' ({{lang-fr|Tour Astro}}, {{lang-nl|Astrotoren}}) is a skyscraper in [[Brussels]], [[Belgium]]. It is located on the northeast corner of the [[small ring (Brussels)|small ring]] in the municipality of [[Saint-Josse-ten-Noode]], just north of the [[Madou Plaza Tower]]. The Astro Tower is {{convert|107|m}} tall, making it one of the [[List of tallest buildings in Belgium|tallest buildings in Belgium]].
The financial firm [[Fortis (finance)|Fortis]] leased the entirety of the building from 2005 to 2011.<ref name = lesoir>{{cite web|title=La tour Astro a été revendue|url=http://www.lesoir.be/regions/bruxelles/immobilier-importante-2008-02-16-577998.shtml|publisher=[[Le Soir]]|date= February 16, 2008|accessdate=August 16, 2009|language=fr}}</ref> From 2011 to 2013, the building underwent extensive renovations.<ref name=emporis/>
The owner, HPG Belgium NV, sold the Astro Tower to Spanish investor Luresa in April 2008.
