'''Dörmögő Dömötör''' is a fictional bear, created by Hungarian novelist [[Zsigmond Sebők]] and comparable to [[Winnie the Pooh]]. ''Dörmögő Dömötör'' is also a children's magazine established in 1957 by state-owned ''Ifjúsági Lapkiadó''.<ref>[http://setaria.oszk.hu/peldinfo_spring/peldinfo.htm?id=1000867&language=hu&view=1 National Széchényi Library catalog of the periodical]</ref> The magazine's mascot is the aforementioned bear, but it presents many different kind of stories, comics, puzzles, and others not related to the bear. The magazine is one of the best selling magazines of publisher [[Drize Publishing Ltd.]]
