The '''Khujand clan''', also known as the '''Leninabad clan''', is the name given to  political alliance based in [[Khujand]], [[Tajikistan]]. The clan largely controlled the [[Government of Tajikistan]] from  [[World War II]] until the [[Tajik Civil War]].<ref name=CONTROL>[http://ismaili.net/mirrors/112_tajik/tajkethn.html Language and Ethnicity Issues in Tajikistan] Heritage Society</ref>

[[Rahmon Nabiyev]], a member of the Khujand clan, became the [[President of Tajikistan]] in November 1991. He served until August 1992 when he was forced to resign at gunpoint.<ref>''[https://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN0415305772&id=g4Ip5X_v0OYC&pg=PA140&lpg=PA140&ots=OvNGBCV-C6&dq=Tajik+Civil+War&sig=oORXc7G3_fSsR9qIMu6KiRH_5NA#PPA141,M1 Russian Foreign Policy and the Cis: Theories, Debates and Actions]'', page 141</ref><ref>''[http://faculty.oxy.edu/richmond/dwa278/tajikistan.htm,DWA 278:Oil and Politics in the Caspian Basin]''</ref>

