[[File:Hansehausantwerpen.jpg|thumb|The Oostershuis in Antwerp]]

The '''Oostershuis''' (Dutch for ''Eastern House'') was a [[kontor]] in [[Antwerp]] and a headquarters of the [[Hanseatic League]].

Designed by [[Cornelis Floris II]], it was erected about 1560 and destroyed by fire in 1893.

