{{infobox Organization |name = [[File:Task force logo.jpg|250px|Task Force on Financial Integrity and Economic Development]] |image = Task_Force_Logo_No_Name.jpg |caption = |abbreviation = Task Force |motto = |formation = 2009<ref>{{cite news|last=Mathiason|first=Nick|title=Britain reluctant to join crackdown on tax havens|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2009/jan/22/tax-avoidance-havens-uk|accessdate=3 May 2011|newspaper=The Guardian|date=22 January 2009}}</ref> |type = Coalition of [[NGOs]] and [[Governments]] |headquarters = 1100 17th Street, NW, Suite 505 |location = [[Washington, D.C.]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |website = [http://www.financialtaskforce.org www.financialtaskforce.org] }}
The '''Task Force on Financial Integrity and Economic Development''' was a unique global coalition of civil society organizations and governments launched in 2009 to address inequalities in the financial system that penalize billions of people. The Task Force was renamed the [[Financial Transparency Coalition]] in May 2013.<ref>{{cite news|last=Rubenfeld|first=Samuel|title=Corruption Currents: From Vatican Bank Image Redux to Adopting Rules|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/riskandcompliance/2013/05/31/corruption-currents-from-vatican-bank-image-redux-to-adopting-rules/|accessdate=30 January 2014|newspaper=Wall Street Journal|date=31 May 2014}}</ref>
